Description: ROSE Link - Home VPN Router for Raspberry Pi with Monitoring
 ROSE Link transforms your Raspberry Pi (3, 4, 5, Zero 2W) into a secure
 VPN router and WiFi access point for your home network.
 .
 Key Features:
  * Connect to Internet via Ethernet (priority) or WiFi client (fallback)
  * Establish WireGuard VPN tunnel to your Fritz!Box or VPN server
  * Create a local WiFi hotspot for your devices (2.4GHz and 5GHz)
  * Route all client traffic through the VPN tunnel
  * Modern web interface for easy configuration
  * Built-in Grafana + Prometheus monitoring dashboard
 .
 Monitoring Stack (Optional):
  * Prometheus for metrics collection
  * Node Exporter for system metrics
  * Grafana for dashboard visualization
  * Pre-configured alerts for VPN, WAN, CPU, Memory, Disk
  * Enable with: rose-monitoring enable
 .
 Supported Hardware:
  * Raspberry Pi 5 - Full support with WiFi 6 and 5GHz
  * Raspberry Pi 4 - Full support with WiFi 5 and 5GHz
  * Raspberry Pi 3 - Limited support (2.4GHz WiFi only)
  * Raspberry Pi Zero 2 W - Basic support (light usage)
 .
 Security Features:
  * Automatic kill-switch (blocks traffic if VPN disconnects)
  * VPN watchdog with auto-reconnection
  * WPA2/WPA3 WiFi encryption
  * HTTPS web interface with TLS 1.2/1.3
  * Minimal sudo permissions for service account
 .
 Compatible with Debian 11 (Bullseye), Debian 12 (Bookworm), and
 Raspberry Pi OS based on these versions.
